Sentencas: This work presents study of the doping effect of M = Cu, Co, and Mo on the cathode properties of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+delta.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In particular, four compositions are prepared by a modified sol-gel method, e.g., Nd1.5Pr0.5NiO4+delta (NPN), Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni0.9Cu0.1O4+delta (NPNCu), Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni0.9Co0.1O4+delta (NPNCo), and Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni0.95Mo0.05O4+delta (NPNMo).
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The crystal structure, phase stability, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), and electrochemical performance of the oxides are systematically investigated.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: No chemical reactions between NPN, NPNCu, NPNCo, and NPNMo cathodes and Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 electrolyte are found.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The average TEC values of the NPN, NPNCu, NPNCo, and NPNMo are determined to be 13.9 x 10(-6) K-1, 13.6 x 10(-6)
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: K-1, 14.7 x 10(-6) K-1, and 13.2 x 10(-6) K-1 in the range of 30-1000 degrees C, close to that of the typical electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: NPN and NPNCu cathodes exhibit very low interfacial polarization resistance value of 0.033 and 0.032 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, which translates to superior fuel cell performance, e.g., peak power density of 456 and 443 mW cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance, however, could be significantly degraded by the Co and Mo doping in the Ni site.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The presented results demonstrate that NPN and NPNCu are promising cathode candidate for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Assessment of Nd1.5Pr0.5Ni1-xMxO4+δ (M = Cu, Co, Mo; x=0, 0.05 and 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell
